- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the equivalence relation between transducers, which can be viewed as a logical relation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the undecidability of the containment relation, which is a common topic in algorithmic complexity theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also possible as the paper uses a syntactical characterization for containment, which can be viewed as an information-theoretic approach. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with transducers, which are used in programming language theory and implementation.
